text:

Bushwick Ave., south side, west from Hart to Jefferson Streets, showing in the background, the steeple of the St. Mark's Church (Evang. Lutheran).

folder: Bushwick Avenue & Hart Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
715-729 Bushwick Ave., north side, at Hart Street (Elm Street). In 1902, the building on the N.W. corner housed the Bushwick Club, in 1916 the Bushwick Democratic Club, and in 1929 the Knights of Columbus.

January 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

text:
729 - 737 Bushwick Avenue, North Side, east from Hart Street.
